== Sweet Potato Chips ==

Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @sweet potato{2} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with
@salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single
layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

== Cucumber Salad ==

Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, mix together the @rice vinegar{15%ml},
@sesame oil{20%ml} and half the @honey{30%ml}.

> If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Trim the @cucumber{1/2}, then pop onto a #board{} and use a #rolling pin{} to
gently smack it a few times until split. Cut into roughly 2cm chunks, then add
to the bowl of dressing. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}, toss
well, then set aside.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).
Trim and thinly slice the @spring onion{2}(thinly sliced).

Thinly slice the @spring greens{150%g}(sliced) widthways.

== Spring Onion Fritters ==

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat.

Add the spring greens and @water{2%tbsp} for the greens, cover with a
tight-fitting #lid{} and cook until wilted, ~{5-6%minutes}. Add the garlic and
@ginger puree{15%ml} and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Season with @salt{} and
@ground black pepper{}.

Crack the @egg{1} into a large #bowl{} and whisk. Add the cooked greens and
half the spring onion. Mix together with the @plain flour{40%g} and
@salt{1/4%tsp}. Season with @ground black pepper{}.

> Lift out some of the mixture with a spoon. If it's too wet and doesn't hold
> its shape, add a little more flour.

Wipe out the (now empty) frying pan and return to a medium-high heat with
enough @oil{} to coat the bottom.

Once the oil is hot, place heaped tablespoons of the fritter mixture (in
batches) into the pan. Flatten slightly with the back of the #spoon{}, then
fry until golden and cooked through, ~{3-4%minutes} each side.

> Don't flip them too early, they need time to set.

Once cooked, transfer to a #plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{}.

Keep cooking in batches until all the mixture is used up - you should get
3-4 fritters per person.

> Add extra oil in between batches if needed.

== Tonkatsu Style Sauce ==

While the fritters fry, make your tonkatsu style sauce.

In a #small saucepan{}, mix together the @soy sauce{25%ml}, @Worcester sauce{15%ml}
and remaining honey with the @tomato ketchup{2%tbsp} and @water{2%tbsp} for the
sauce.

Pop on medium heat and bring to the boil, then reduce the heat until
simmering. Cook until thickened, ~{3-4%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

== To Serve ==

When everything's ready, transfer your okonomiyaki inspired fritters to your
plates.

Drizzle each fritter with the tonkatsu style sauce, then sprinkle over the
remaining spring onion.

Serve your sweet potato chips and cucumber salad alongside.

Enjoy!